	(text "USB-C Connector Notes:\n\nVBUS (A4/B4): 5V from USB host — powers CH340N\nCC1, CC2: MUST have 5.1kΩ pull-down each to GND\n  (required for USB-C host to supply power; Rd = 5.1kΩ)\nD+/D-: USB 2.0 full-speed data (12 Mbit/s)\nSBU1, SBU2: no connect (not used)\nShield: connect to GND via 1MΩ (chassis ground isolation)\n\nNo USB PD circuitry needed — 5V at 500mA from\na standard USB 2.0 port is sufficient.\nFor USB 3.0 or higher, the SS pins are unused;\nthis connector only uses USB 2.0 lanes."
		(at 100 40 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000004-text-0000-0000-000000000001")
	)

	(text "CH340N Notes:\n\nInternal 12 MHz oscillator — no crystal needed.\nVCC: 5V (from VBUS)\nV3: 3.3V output (bypass with 100nF)\n  Can power MSPM0 (max ~50mA) if Pi absent,\n  but requires diode-OR to avoid back-driving Pi 3.3V.\nTXD: CH340 transmits → MSPM0 PA11 (RX) via SB1\nRXD: CH340 receives ← MSPM0 PA10 (TX) via SB2\n~DTR: can be connected to MSPM0 NRST for auto-reset\n  on firmware upload; leave NC if not needed.\n\nUART sharing with Pi:\nSB1 (0Ω, TX path) and SB2 (0Ω, RX path) allow\ndisconnecting the CH340 UART when the Pi is in use.\nBy default both are installed. Only one source should\ndrive the MSPM0 UART RX line at a time."
		(at 100 80 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000004-text-0000-0000-000000000002")
	)

